<li id="custom_ads-23" class="widget Custom_Ads"><div class="htlad-LH_PP_RR"></div></li>
<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">January 22, 2024</h2>
<a href="/lit-hub-daily-january-22-2024/"><img class="wp-image-232274 size-thumbnail aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Screenshot-2024-01-21-at-9.09.01-PM-150x150.png" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://www.newyorker.com/culture/postscript/lev-rubinstein-a-devoted-and-defiant-lover-of-language" class="external" target="_blank">Masha Gessen remembers Lev Rubinstein</a>, Russian poet and essayist, who died last week at 76.</li>
 	<li>B.J. Novak <a href="https://www.theparisreview.org/blog/2024/01/19/caps-for-sale/#more-166563" class="external" target="_blank">considers <em>Caps for Sale</em></a>.</li>
 	<li>Lincoln Michel on <a href="https://countercraft.substack.com/p/on-reviewing-books" class="external" target="_blank">the difficulty of reviewing books</a>.</li>
</ul>
<a title="LitHub Daily: May 1, 2015" href="/lit-hub-daily-january-22-2024/"><button>More News</button></a></li>
	    			</ul>
	    		</div>
